        "management": "CG equation: CrCl (mL/min) = [(140 - age) x ABW] / (72 x SCr) x 0.85 if female. For obesity (BMI >30), use adjusted body weight (AdjBW = IBW + 0.4 x (ABW - IBW)). For all drug dosing decisions, use CG over eGFR. Adjust drug interval or dose based on CrCl thresholds specific to each drug."
