          { "feature": "both_report_as_ml_min_1_point_73_m2_not_corrected_bsa", "weight": 4 },
          { "feature": "neither_preferred_for_drug_dosing_by_fda", "weight": 4 }
        ],
        "management": "Use CKD-EPI for CKD staging (KDIGO guidelines). For drug dosing, convert eGFR to CG equivalent or use BSA-unadjusted values. When eGFR <60, always use CG for dosing decisions. For chemotherapy carboplatin, use Calvert formula with CG-based CrCl."
