          { "feature": "protein_binding_above_90_percent_minimizes_removal", "weight": 5 },
          { "feature": "large_vd_above_2_L_per_kg_limits_dialytic_clearance", "weight": 4 },
          { "feature": "post_dialysis_supplemental_dose_needed_for_some_drugs", "weight": 4 }
        ],
        "management": "Drugs significantly removed by HD: aminoglycosides, vancomycin, levetiracetam, metronidazole. Give after dialysis or supplement. Drugs NOT removed: amiodarone, ceftriaxone, phenytoin, warfarin (high protein binding). For CRRT, use eCrCl = 15-25 + UF rate for dosing approximations."
