        "management": "Aminoglycosides: once-daily dosing, monitor peak/trough. Vancomycin: target AUC/MIC 400-600, trough 15-20 for serious infections. Avoid triple whammy: ACEi/ARB + diuretic + NSAID. Hold metformin if CrCl <30. Hold SGLT2i if CrCl <45. Monitor SCr and urine output q8h in AKI."
